Gauteng Department of Education sends condolences to family of late King Edward VII learner 8 February 2022 The Gauteng Department of Education (GDE) confirms with sadness, the tragic passing of a Grade 11 King Edward VII learner on Sunday 6 February 2022. The learner unfortunately died following a stabbing allegedly at a Rivonia night club. The alleged perpetrator has been arrested and the matter is being followed up by relevant law enforcement agencies. “Our thoughts right now are with the family, friends and fellow learners of the late Grade 11 learner. We convey our deepest condolences to the parents of the deceased learner and wish them strength during this challenging period,” MEC Lesufi said. The Gauteng Department of Education (GDE) has already provided psycho-social support to the family and friends of the late learner. Issued by Oupa Bodibe, Acting Spokesperson for the Gauteng Department of Education, 8 February 2022